The wireframe
A wireframe is a simple visual layout that shows the structure of an app or website,
without colors or detailed design.
It focuses on the placement of content, buttons, and navigation to test ideas
and improve usability before creating a realistic mockup.
This helps designers and developers organize information clearly and ensures
a smooth user experience.
Wireframes are essential tools for planning before adding detailed graphics
and interactivity.
Wire Battle
War is a simple card game where each
player turns over one card,and the
higher card wins both cards.
The goal is to win all the cards.
THE STEPS TO CREATING A WIREFRAME.
A wireframe is an essential tool in web and app design because it helps organize
content and functionality before adding visual details.
